    "created_at": "2017-02-22T17:45:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-02-22T17:45:03Z",
    "body": "I believe this is a limitation of the macOS API being used.\r\n\r\nElectron uses a [NSAlert](https://developer.apple.com/reference/appkit/nsalert?language=objc) and the docs state:\r\n\r\n> Any button with a title of “Cancel” has a key equivalent of Escape, and any button with the title “Don’t Save” has a key equivalent of Command-D (but only if it is not the first button)\r\n\r\nhttps://developer.apple.com/reference/appkit/nsalert/1532992-buttons?language=objc\r\n\r\nSo I'm going to close this out since this is the expected behavior for a message box on macOS.\r\n\r\nUsing a modal `BrowserWindow` could be an option you can pursue to have complete control over the styling and behavior of this."
  },
